HEADWORD: Mucker
<hw>Muck"er</hw> <pr>(m⟦ucr⟧k"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A term
of reproach for a low or vulgar labor person.</def>
<mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mucker</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: mucker
<hw>muck"er</hw> <pr>(m⟦ucr⟧k"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Construction)</fld> <def>An excavating machine designed to remove
particulate material from within a confined area, as in a tunnel or
mine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>RDH</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mucker</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Mucker
<hw>Muck"er</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To scrape together, as money, by
mean labor or shifts.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Udall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muckerer</ent>⟦br⟧
